From: backport of authlib/joserfc#96
Subject: Normalize P-521 test fixture for cryptography 47+

cryptography 47+ rejects this PEM because the P-521 private scalar
was encoded as 65 bytes, while P-521 requires a fixed 66-byte private
key value. This re-encodes the same key material with the correct
length so newer cryptography can load it.

diff --git a/tests/keys/ec-p512-private.pem b/tests/keys/ec-p512-private.pem
index 5ebaff2e..9ec1818b 100644
--- a/tests/keys/ec-p512-private.pem
